---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Support"
  description="Install help, troubleshooting, and contact for RevAudio plugins."
>
  <section class="plugin-detail">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;" data-reveal>
      <h1>Support &amp; install</h1>
      <p class="pitch">Quick install, common fixes, and how to reach us when things go sideways.</p>

      <h3>Install (Windows)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Download the installer from the confirmation email sent to you after checkout.</li>
        <li>Run the installer and accept the licence terms.</li>
        <li>Plugins install to their standard locations:
          <ul>
            <li>VST3: <code>C:\Program Files\Common Files\VST3\</code></li>
            <li>AAX: <code>C:\Program Files\Common Files\Avid\Audio\Plug-Ins\</code></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Open your DAW and rescan plugins. RevAudio plugins appear under the <strong>RevAudio</strong> manufacturer.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Install (macOS)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Download the macOS installer from the confirmation email sent to you after checkout.</li>
        <li>Run the installer and accept the licence terms.</li>
        <li>Plugins install to their standard locations:
          <ul>
            <li>VST3: <code>/Library/Audio/Plug-Ins/VST3/</code></li>
            <li>AU: <code>/Library/Audio/Plug-Ins/Components/</code></li>
            <li>AAX: <code>/Library/Application Support/Avid/Audio/Plug-Ins/</code></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Open your DAW and rescan plugins. RevAudio plugins appear under the <strong>RevAudio</strong> manufacturer.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Activate your licence</h3>
      <p>
        On first launch, the plugin asks for your licence key. The key was emailed to you right after
        checkout. Paste it in once &mdash; it is stored locally and reused on every subsequent launch.
      </p>
      <p>
        Lost your key? Email <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> with the address you
        purchased under and we&rsquo;ll resend.
      </p>

      <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>The DAW does not see the plugin after install</summary>
        <p>
          Restart your DAW or trigger a manual plugin rescan. Confirm the plugin files exist at the
          paths listed in the Install section above for your format (VST3, AU, or AAX).
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Crash or audio dropout</summary>
        <p>
          Send a brief email to <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a> with: DAW + version,
          OS version, sample rate + buffer size, and a description of what you were doing when it happened.
          We respond within one business day.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>The DAW does not see the plugin on macOS</summary>
        <p>
          Restart your DAW or trigger a plugin rescan. In Logic Pro, open the plug-in manager under
          Settings. In Ableton Live, go to Preferences → Plug-Ins. Confirm the files exist at the
          paths listed in the Install (macOS) section above. On Apple Silicon Macs, make sure your
          DAW is not running under Rosetta.
        </p>
      </details>

      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>
        General: <a href="mailto:hello@revaudio.net">hello@revaudio.net</a><br/>
        Support: <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a><br/>
        Press: <a href="mailto:press@revaudio.net">press@revaudio.net</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  details {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-1);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  details summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--brass-bright);
  }

  details[open] summary { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  ol { color: var(--fg-dim); }
  ol li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
</style>
